CONTEXT ARM20Test2 IN DUTCH
--$ This test validates that field expressions must be wider than the view concept
------------------------------------------------------------
PATTERN ARM20Test2

RELATION critBF[Criterium*Bedrijfsfunctie] [MAP] PRAGMA "" " wordt gehanteerd binnen "
RELATION bfCrit[Bedrijfsfunctie*Criterium] [MAP] PRAGMA "" " heeft als criterium "
CLASSIFY Criterium ISA Verwachting
RELATION expID[Verwachting*ExpectationID] [MAP] PRAGMA "" "staat in de business bekend als"

VIEW Verwachtingen: Verwachting(critBF, bfCrit~, expID)
{- Errors expected for VIEW Verwachtingen:
.../Ampersand/testing/Travis/testcases/Check/ShouldFail/ARM20-Test2.adl:11:33 error:
  The expression in a VIEW segment is too narrow for the VIEW concept.
    Expression: critBF[Criterium*Bedrijfsfunctie]
    VIEW concept: Verwachting
    The source of the expression (Criterium) is more specific than the VIEW concept (Verwachting).
    A VIEW expression must work for all instances of the VIEW concept, not just a subset.
------------------------------
.../Ampersand/testing/Travis/testcases/Check/ShouldFail/ARM20-Test2.adl:11:41 error:
  The expression in a VIEW segment is too narrow for the VIEW concept.
    Expression: bfCrit[Bedrijfsfunctie*Criterium]~
    VIEW concept: Verwachting
    The source of the expression (Criterium) is more specific than the VIEW concept (Verwachting).
    A VIEW expression must work for all instances of the VIEW concept, not just a subset.
-}

VIEW Bedrijfsfuncties: Bedrijfsfunctie(critBF~, bfCrit)
{- No errors expected -}
ENDPATTERN
------------------------------------------------------------
ENDCONTEXT
